<!--
    PUF France Use Case 8: Invoice Paid to Third Party - Classic Factoring
    (Facture à payer à un tiers déterminé au moment de la facturation - Affacturage)
    
    Business Scenario:
    - SELLER has assigned invoice receivable to Factor (invoice financing)
    - Factor becomes legal owner of receivable before invoice transmission
    - BUYER must pay Factor directly (not SELLER)
    - Classic factoring with Factor disclosure to BUYER
    
    Key Requirements:
    - Business process B1: Standard invoice
    - Invoice type code: 393 (Factored invoice)
    - BG-10 PAYEE: Factor information (BT-59, BT-60, BT-61)
    - EXT-FR-FE-26: "DL" (Delegatee - Factor role qualification)
    - BG-17 Payment: Factor's IBAN (BT-84)
    - BT-21 "ACC": Subrogation/assignment note code
    - BT-22: Legal subrogation text (Dailly law notice)
    - Amount due payable to Factor
    
    Financial Flow:
    - Invoice total: 5000.00 EUR (net) + 1000.00 EUR VAT = 6000.00 EUR
    - BUYER pays: 6000.00 EUR to Factor
    - Factor advances: ~80-90% to SELLER immediately
    - Factor retains: ~10-20% reserve until payment received
    - Factor settles: Reserve to SELLER after BUYER payment (minus fees)
    
    Workflow:
    1. SELLER assigns receivable to Factor (Dailly law assignment)
    2. SELLER creates e-invoice with Factor as PAYEE
    3. BUYER receives invoice via PPF platform
    4. BUYER pays Factor directly (Factor's IBAN in BT-84)
    5. Factor receives payment from BUYER
    6. Factor settles final reserve to SELLER (minus factoring fees)
    
    French Text Codes (BT-21/BT-22):
    - #REG#: Company legal form and share capital
    - #ABL#: Trade register number (RCS)
    - #AAI#: APE business activity code
    - #PMD#: Late payment penalties (payable to Factor)
    - #PMT#: Fixed collection costs indemnity (€40 - payable to Factor)
    - #BAR#: Treatment type (B2B e-invoicing)
    - ACC: Subrogation/assignment legal notice (Dailly law)
-->
